This paper primarily focuses on the privacy and security risks posed by adware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the technical capabilities of the adware, including traffic interception and browser process injection, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and system and information theory (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the prevalence of the adware through the popularity of its domains, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
